            <p> This letter, written by William B. Anderson to his wife Louisa, is part of a collecton from the Rare Books and 
               Manuscripts Department at the Ohio State University Main Library in Columbus, Ohio. Most of the William B. Anderson letters describe
               his daily tasks as a riverboat captain during the Civil War through basic correspondance with his wife. This particular letter, written on August 16, 1862,
               is a heartfelt note that reveals emotion and grief about
            Anderson's occupation as a riverboat captain.  Anderson's job was to board soldiers and take them away to where they were needed. He wrote
               to his wife about how saddened he is to take these men away from their families. The William B. Anderson letters
            are useful in constructing a personal view of life during the Civil War. Though textbooks and objective sources about the Civil War are informative
            and helpful, the William B. Anderson Letters provide a personal touch for the reader and present a sentiment that may not be
               present in objective sources. </p>
            <p>This letter is significant because
            it allows the reader to relate to Anderson and understand his hardships and feelings. In David Levys's Scrolling Forward, Levy discusses how letters
            are a gateway to one's feelings. A letter "addresses a highly personal subject; and in its hand-produced marks it expresses some of the 
            drama and pathos of the situation in which it is embedded" (Levy, 80&ndash;81). While examining the William B. Anderson letters, it is important for the reader to search the images provided
            and see these hand-produced marks that reveal a certain degree of vulnerability in the author. Though electronic editions can at times lose the personal touch of the letters, the reader is
            encouraged to search the images and visit the Rare Books and Manuscripts Department at the Ohio State University Main Library. </p>
            <p><hi rend="bold">Works Cited</hi></p>
            <p>Levy, David M. <title level="m">Scrolling Forward: Making Sense of Documents in the Digital
               Age</title>. New York: Arcade, 2001.</p>
            
